{"hits": {"hits": [{"created": "2026-04-20T18:59:12.572523+00:00", "modified": "2026-04-20T18:59:13.126146+00:00", "id": 19669406, "conceptrecid": "19669405", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.19669406", "conceptdoi": "10.5281/zenodo.19669405", "doi_url": "https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19669406", "metadata": {"title": "New record of the Wroughton's Free-tailed Bat (Otomops wroughtoni) and its activity in the vicinity of wind turbines in western India", "doi": "10.5281/zenodo.19669406", "publication_date": "2025", "description": "(Uploaded by Plazi for the Bat Literature Project) Otomops wroughtoni is one of the rarest and most enigmatic species of bats in South and Southeast Asia. The species was first discovered from Barepede caves in Karnataka, India. In subsequent years a single individual was reported from Cambodia followed by discoveries of a few roosts in Northeast India. The species was initially classified as Critically Endangered but later it was moved to Data Deficient category in the IUCN status due to the lack of knowledge regarding its habitat, breeding, diet, distribution and population. The species is also listed in the schedule I of The Wildlife (Protection) Amendment Act, 2022 granting it the highest level of protection in India. We report a new distribution record of Otomops wroughtoni from the northern part of the Western Ghats, 250km north from its previously known distribution. We recorded 69 acoustic detections of the species over 54 nights while comparing bat activity in areas with and without wind turbines. The presence of this protected bat species within a wind farm raises critical concerns, as wind farms are a known global threat to open-space foraging bats. This study reinstates the value of acoustic surveys in identifying the distribution of data-deficient, high-altitude, open-space foraging bats. As the only recordings of individuals away from known roosts, our observations provide an understanding of the natural history and habitat of a poorlyknown species.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Jayakumar, Sreejith", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Chakravarty, Rohit", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/645309cd83634aeec54a072d2f0bf28c", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/ab270181fe328e36058a89b928def358f5ec800b11a7005fe341700f6d30c574", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/NGXCGD75", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/NGXCGD75", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/bd73f4923c6928eb0af08c91aebcee69!/b372954-375470", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/0157e8ec3f1f8eb877e7b6cd6fde26bc", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.1410543", "relation": "isCompiledBy", "resource_type": "software", "scheme": "doi"}], "custom": {"dwc:class": ["Mammalia"], "dwc:kingdom": ["Animalia"], "dwc:order": ["Chiroptera"], "dwc:phylum": ["Chordata"]}, "resource_type": {"title": "Journal article", "type": "publication", "subtype": "article"}, "journal": {"issue": "1", "pages": "67-72", "title": "Barbastella", "volume": "18"}, "alternate_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/645309cd83634aeec54a072d2f0bf28c"}, {"identifier": "urn:lsid:zotero.org:groups:5435545:items:NGXCGD75"}, {"identifier": "10.14709/BarbJ.18.1.2025.08"}], "communities": [{"id": "batlit"}, {"id": "biosyslit"}], "relations": {"version": [{"index": 0, "is_last": true, "parent": {"pid_type": "recid", "pid_value": "19669405"}}]}}, "title": "New record of the Wroughton's Free-tailed Bat (Otomops wroughtoni) and its activity in the vicinity of wind turbines in western India", "links": {"self": "https://zenodo.org/api/reco